  "problemPrompt": "A 0.600 g impure magnesium sample reacts with excess hydrochloric acid: Mg + 2HCl → MgCl2 + H2. The hydrogen collected at room conditions has a volume of 480 cm3. Use molar gas volume 24 000 cm3 mol−1 and Ar(Mg)=24.0. Calculate the percentage purity of the magnesium sample.",
  "requiredEvidence": {
